721216f-a.text:
Madison Ave., east side, from but not including 25th to
and including 26th Streets, a part of Madison Scuare Garden shown

About 1923.

721212f-a.title: Manhattan: Madison Avenue - 25th Street (East)
721212f-a.text:
25 to 17 Madison Ave., at, adjoining and south of the S.E. corner of
East 25th Street, showing the demolition of 3 buildings that stood here.
They were the Madison Ave., the Farragut and the Pullman Buildings. The
Metropolitan Life Insurance Co., whose Annex occupies the balance of this
block will utilize this site for construction.
September 1, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
